Character Counts
Character Counts and Safe School Week is October 21-25 (N.J.S.A. 18A: 36-5.1). During the week of Oct. 21st., students will be taking part in learning age appropriate ways to further assist in understanding and preventing harrassment, intimidation and bullying.

post_text: Week of Respect is October 7-11. (The Anti-Bullying Bill of Rights Act - PL 2010, c.122). Throughout the State of NJ, the week of October 7th has been designated the WEEK OF RESPECT, devoted to teaching students about tolerance and acceptance of others through Character Education.

post_text:
MVS welcomes nurse, Mrs. DeCostanza!

Greetings Mountain Villa Family!

My name is Mrs. Jodie DeCostanza and I am the new School Nurse. I have 30 years overall nursing experience and 10 years of School Nurse experience. I have experience in grades Pre-k through 12, with an emphasis on elementary education. I am also a certified American Heart Association CPR and First Aid Instructor.

I am very excited to join the Mountain Villa community and I look forward to working with the students and families at Mountain Villa School.

Feel free to contact me at any time with questions or concerns. I can be reached as follows:

908-852-1894 X303 or jdecostanza@aes.k12.nj.us

I wish you a happy, healthy summer!



Jodie DeCostanza
